-the mode need to be specifoed 
If your hash starts with...,It is likely...,Use Mode (-m)
$2y$ or $2a$,Bcrypt (Blowfish),3200
$P$ or $H$,Phpass / WordPress,400
$1$,MD5 (Unix),500
No special characters (32 hex chars),Plain MD5,0
"* (e.g., *0945...)",Old MySQL Password,300

sudo hashcat -m [MODE_NUMBER] pass.txt /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt

sudo gunzip /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt.gz (incase rockyou.txt is not unzipped)

