now have to see what all services are running
command for that is 
systemctl list-units --type=service --state=running

🔹 systemctl
Command used to interact with systemd
systemd = the system manager that controls services in Linux
👉 Think:
“Tool to control and inspect services”
🔹 list-units
Tells systemctl to list units
❓ What is a “unit”?
A unit is any object managed by systemd:
service
socket
mount
timer
👉 So this means:
“Show me all systemd-managed things”
🔹 --type=service
Filters the output
👉 Only show:
services (not sockets, mounts, etc.)
So now:
“Show me only services”
🔹 --state=running
Another filter
👉 Only show services that are:
currently running (active)
So now:
“Show me only services that are currently running”

